{"TopicId":219846,"ForumId":201,"TopicTitle":"Airbrake Drag Cube is Treated as a Freestanding Part Regardless of Condition (Deployed/Undeployed)","CreatedByName":"hidearimjosh","CreatedById":226610,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-10T00:50:32Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"hidearimjosh","CreatedById":226610,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-10T00:50:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.1.4.1 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Emicro engineer | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Windows 10 Home edition (Build 19045.3324) | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Intel i7-9700 | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0NVIDIA GeForce GTX 1660 Ti | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E16 GB 2666 Hz\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe drag created by airbrakes does not change when deployed or undeployed. This issues causes large sums of drag to be caused by airbrakes while the airbrakes are at any angle other than 0 relative to the oncoming wind regardless of being deployed or not.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nA workspace file has been included with the 2 planes used for testing.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nExpected result: Drag created by a surface mounted, undeployed, airbrake should not increase as the craft pitches up as the airbrake is out of the airstream and flat against the body.\u003Cbr\u003E\nCurrent result:\u00A0The game applies drag to the airbrakes on their \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Angle of Attack\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Angle of Attack\u0022\u003EAoA\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E alone while disregarding their relative position to the fuselage of the plane\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nExpected result: Left\u003Cbr\u003E\nCurrent result: Right\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022image.png?ex=65370884\u0026amp;is=65249384\u0026amp;hm=bb2\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002250.00\u0022 height=\u0022584\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/1039965578754007060/1161090205252603934/image.png?ex=65370884\u0026amp;is=65249384\u0026amp;hm=bb2dd989006209c7716bd8f12a1ceb74122849958e578e3eea82dfee6e00c822\u0026amp;=\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nTesting to prove the theory. All testing was done by letting the plane achieve the highest speed it can in any given state, making sure it was stable, and then taking a screenshot.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nPlane WITHOUT airbrakes (\u003Cstrong\u003E405 m/s\u003C/strong\u003E)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022planetest_nobrakes.PNG?ex=65370559\u0026amp;is=65\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002258.42\u0022 height=\u0022651\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/1039965578754007060/1161086801730080778/planetest_nobrakes.PNG?ex=65370559\u0026amp;is=65249059\u0026amp;hm=9c7777548acd2dd51dac477579bed1a7a85b23cf695da994c503637494c5628f\u0026amp;=\u0026amp;width=1291\u0026amp;height=701\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nPlane with airbrakes on the side (undeployed (\u003Cstrong\u003E361m/s\u003C/strong\u003E) and deployed (\u003Cstrong\u003E187m/s\u003C/strong\u003E))\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022planetest_brakesonside.PNG?ex=6537053b\u0026amp;i\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002258.25\u0022 height=\u0022674\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/1039965578754007060/1161086674269376563/planetest_brakesonside.PNG?ex=6537053b\u0026amp;is=6524903b\u0026amp;hm=8cecd6d4e88212adb7e4fae5889caddd82bbb0bdf42a10a7360f9c2a96ff6bd2\u0026amp;=\u0026amp;width=1246\u0026amp;height=700\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022planetest_brakesonsidedeployed.PNG?ex=65\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002262.31\u0022 height=\u0022701\u0022 width=\u00221125\u0022 src=\u0022https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/1039965578754007060/1161086674672025660/planetest_brakesonsidedeployed.PNG?ex=6537053b\u0026amp;is=6524903b\u0026amp;hm=4b1b174b61442d76ad3f116d35bf04e01f604ce142e0828fddf70fc19e61a781\u0026amp;=\u0026amp;width=1125\u0026amp;height=701\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlane with airbrakes placed at a 90 degree angle by default (undeployed (\u003Cstrong\u003E188 m/s\u003C/strong\u003E) and deployed (\u003Cstrong\u003E376 m/s\u003C/strong\u003E))\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022planetest_brakesonsidedeployeddefault.PN\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002258.42\u0022 height=\u0022633\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/1039965578754007060/1161086728199741543/planetest_brakesonsidedeployeddefault.PNG?ex=65370547\u0026amp;is=65249047\u0026amp;hm=fdf6c1db31e12b844ff382d4cc42ed997d88c6c90a27698a6a66e497e5500317\u0026amp;=\u0026amp;width=1328\u0026amp;height=701\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022planetest_brakesonsidedeployeddefaultdep\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002255.92\u0022 height=\u0022559\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/1039965578754007060/1161086728489160757/planetest_brakesonsidedeployeddefaultdeployed.PNG?ex=65370548\u0026amp;is=65249048\u0026amp;hm=4e98314c9b6c450706b9fa6bad97241a527720657cd85005fec03f44526b050b\u0026amp;=\u0026amp;width=1440\u0026amp;height=671\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/applications/core/interface/file/cfield.php?storage=form_Fields\u0026amp;path=AirbrakeDragBugreport.json\u0026amp;fileKey=%5B!AES128GCM%5BvheL58B9v7O9rZPWYjSi9WvK2pUKwqIEQGb5XonV5ulljs5QHJn11CQK3VQhTPtVJfQVfM48PxmXCbW9Y0a0yt8I77SDcGVXGHZZ%5D%5B8785ec25d3fc2e3f75aa6509%5D%5B8ff0036ee65713acbe4f1386c101864a%5D%5D\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EAirbrakeDragBugreport.json\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-10-10T00:57:47Z\u0022 title=\u002210/10/2023 12:57  AM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Oct 10\u0022\u003EOctober 10, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Anth12\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Baleygr","CreatedById":231066,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-28T20:46:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.1.5 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Win10 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A05600X | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A03700 | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E64GB\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ESeverity\u003C/strong\u003E:\u00A0Med/Low\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EFrequency\u003C/strong\u003E:\u00A0High/100%\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EDescription\u003C/strong\u003E:\u00A0\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nSteps\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nUse Craft \u0060Airbrake \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Angle of Attack\u0022\u003EAoA\u003C/abbr\u003E Test\u0060 from attached Workspace.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nSet angle of attach for existing Airbrakes as needed (for top mounted, use two compensating the mass)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nLaunch Craft\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nAt MECO (end of runwayish), stage for braking parachutes\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nRecover vessel\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nObserve\u00A0\u00A0max speed\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nRinse Pilot and Repeat\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActual\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\ntop mounted airbrakes are far slower (263 m/s) than side mounted ones (311m(s)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nthere is a non linear relationship between angle of attach and final speed\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExpected\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nSame final speed on\u00A0all mounting points/angle of attach\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nSame drag for\u00A0\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNotes\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFirst I assumed a trigonometric behaviour (see diagram), still might be but could be overshadowed by approaching Mach1\u003Cbr\u003E\nThe second Craft in the Workspace is stuck below Mach1 with a top mounted Airbrake, and reaches \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Low Kerbin Orbit\u0022\u003ELKO\u003C/abbr\u003E with 1k \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003EdV\u003C/abbr\u003E with side mounted ones\u003Cbr\u003E\nBehaviour is not observed for other parts (tested about 10 others, gears, fins, wings, tanks (empty), pilot seat)\u003Cbr\u003E\nBehaviour is not observed for deployed airbreakes (!)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/applications/core/interface/file/cfield.php?storage=form_Fields\u0026amp;path=Airbrakes_braking.mp4\u0026amp;fileKey=%5B!AES128GCM%5B4L1/ciO8/Lvo9PqKta%2BRFgQBbzMF8a9Mr3GuJiQ3yrBoshu9ERdKoSJsGepzR0CZXQxQYMBM9jooBzBc/pexAxPR/pVfCRKrklA=%5D%5B9da44e4b6e2d8ce7abaf2d86%5D%5B4efc31278f826a9a0657d35abc10f41f%5D%5D\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EAirbrakes_braking.mp4\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/applications/core/interface/file/cfield.php?storage=form_Fields\u0026amp;path=NewWorkspace.json\u0026amp;fileKey=%5B!AES128GCM%5BMFZnKSAA4qGrXez4QgGpwg2WzjM5SYqTdQjPTx14z3gwJJ1yGgftdaC456w0O8wNAWGsblZBm/KgPet7Nydauxcd%5D%5B3394eeff626ceea9e316c876%5D%5B837f3619d1ca5155855d8a3201fbb842%5D%5D\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003ENewWorkspace.json\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u0022airbreakes_braking.PNG.6e0ff530bab0538348f373f6cdebcc89.PNG\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/uploads/monthly_2023_10/airbreakes_braking.PNG.6e0ff530bab0538348f373f6cdebcc89.PNG\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003C